Former Force PRO Frank Mba has been appointed again as spokesman by the acting Inspector General of Police Adamu Mohammed.
The assistant commissioner of police takes over from Moshood Jimoh, an acting Deputy Commissioner of Police.
Mba was working at the Special Fraud Unit (SFU), Ikoyi- Lagos, before his latest appointment.
The posting is with immediate effect.
Mr Mba studied law at University of Lagos and the University of Dundee, Scotland, United Kingdom.
He attended the Nigeria Police Academy, Kano and the FBI National Academy, Quantico, USA.
He also holds a Certificate in National and International Security from the Harvard University, USA.
Mba has served at state, national, and international levels, winning accolades, including the UN Medal.
